Subject: Re: [T2] Single notch on the Crank pulley

On Fri, 9 May 2008, Trey Jung wrote:

> on one of my 71 buses... there is only 1 notch filed on the "backside" of the
> crank pulley.. that year the timing was set to 5 degrees ATDC... Someone told
> me that was the notch for the 5 degree timing mark, I assumed it was TDC..

> Anyone have a 71 bus with the original pulley and know the truth?

On a '71, the mark is 5 degrees ATDC, IIRC.

On mine, the front side of the pulley had a "dimple" stamped into it at
TDC, the rear edge had the notch at 5ATDC.  Front is Front!

George
